column1: Today is Small Business Saturday! This year more than ever it's important for us as a community to support our local businesses who have been affected by COVID-19. Let's #ShopSmall! https://t.co/XlHyQXyG86

This is Pam Keith's closing message. Not fighting algal blooms. Not helping our community recover from coronavirus. But cheering on Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and engaging with national political analysts on the election administration in NYC. Pam Keith is #PoliticsBeforePeople. https://t.co/OXWnLpW7BE

During the first several months of the coronavirus pandemic our team helped save more than 65000 jobs in our community by supporting small & local businesses.  I'm proud to be named a "Guardian of Small Business" by @NFIB! https://t.co/tsipZdEhah

Pam Keith supports hiking taxes by an average of more than $3000 per family.  In the midst of the economic recovery from coronavirus the last thing people need is a tax increase! https://t.co/AKSBpdwwAU

Pam Keith's plan to immediately raise taxes by more than $3000 per family would be a disaster. I will continue to fight for lower taxes with a laser focus on the unique needs of our community as the coronavirus recovery continues. https://t.co/2SmQFYst4P

During coronavirus my team and I helped 20000+ people in #FL18 with unemployment small business loans and more. Fair question to ask: what would Pam Keith have done to help when she says "You don’t give me your vote or your money I don’t gotta listen to you"? https://t.co/qR50cN8fn7

What happened when coronavirus hit... 1) Our team individually assisted more than 20000 people & helped save more than 65000 jobs in #FL18 2) Pam Keith incited violence against her political opponents suggesting an “open season” on conservatives. https://t.co/bCHktOfOvI

Our team has worked around the clock during the coronavirus pandemic and through the Paycheck Protection Program we helped save more than 65000 jobs in our community. I will keep fighting with everything I've got to help EVERYONE in our community - people before politics! https://t.co/cIn7mK8nzj
China owes a debt and needs to be held accountable for the part they played in the coronavirus. If you agree sign the petition: https://t.co/zGJLcM1JgU

China owes a debt to the world because of their disgraceful handling of the coronavirus pandemic that has cost so many lives and countless economic damage.  As a Member of the Congressional-Executive Commission on China I am committed to holding them accountable! https://t.co/2t8MW0uJtD
As we rebuild our economy from coronavirus I will continue to be a champion for small businesses and I am proud to have the support of the U.S. Chamber of Commerce! https://t.co/2vMVhLkZs6

Thank you to EMTs and emergency medical services providers across our state and nation for being a reliable source of strength in times of need. During EMS Week and especially with the coronavirus epidemic we thank you for all that you do! https://t.co/8xrsRxkLXj
I am working to make sure Florida's produce growers have the resources they need to survive and feed our communities during the #COVID19 crisis! https://t.co/FRKtgZbeqo
To stay up to date with all information regarding the coronavirus from the @CDCgov you can go to: https://t.co/DtOAwL7vBU. https://t.co/rAvxvpuDKm

On National Doctor's Day today I wanted to take this opportunity to personally thank all doctors and healthcare workers who have been working tirelessly to combat coronavirus. Let us all make an effort to thank them for their service during this time! https://t.co/q2p4uAQw0O
ICYMI - I sat down with Michael Williams and an infectious disease expert to discuss the coronavirus pandemic. You can watch here: https://t.co/vmE9GtIKXn
